A truck driver was yesterday charged with stealing electricity installation equipment worth Sh20 million.  Joseph Karanja was accused of stealing  six electrical conductor drums from Joseph Johanna between August 8 and 21. Karanja had been hired by Johanna to move the equipment from Longonot to Marti in Samburu county. He was also charged with handling stolen goods and vandalism of electrical apparatus. The court heard that Karanja willfully and unlawfully damaged the six drums of aluminium conductors wire measuring 15, 000 metres  by cutting them into peaces without authority of the complainant. Karanja denied the charges. The case will be mentioned on September 10 before hearing on September 17.     